OL,6,FDeputy Farnham adds: "Jersey is an
OL,7,Finclusive, tolerant, and respectful
OL,8,Fsociety. There is no place here for
OL,9,Fmessages of hate or division. Such
OL,10,Fbehaviour not only damages property,
OL,11,Fbut it attempts to undermine the very
OL,12,Fvalues that bind us together: mutual
OL,13,Frespect, dignity, and compassion."
OL,15,FThe head of the Jersey Jewish
OL,16,FCongregation, Martha Bernstein, says
OL,17,Fshe is "disappointed and shocked" by
OL,18,Fthe widespread graffiti, adding that
OL,19,Fit "stirs up unpleasant memories" for
OL,20,Fthose who lived through the Nazi
OL,21,FOccupation of the Channel Islands.
